aliases.name: ParsedLog
aliases.comment:
Alias to represent parsed log.

Tag is part of the log message before the first colon.

values.name: parseWithOptionalTag
values.comment:
Try to parse Debug.log message including the tag. If it is not parsable, try to parse it without the tag.

This one is safer, but it might be slow due to the fact that it is trying two approaches. It should be used with caution.

name: DebugParser.ElmValue
comment: @docs ElmValue, ExpandableValue, PlainValue, SequenceType, toggle, hasNestedValues

unions.name: ElmValue
unions.comment:
Elm values that are parsed can be either plain values like Strings and Bools, or they can be expandable values like Records, Dicts etc.

Expandable values has bool as their first parameter, which is used to indicate whether they are expanded or collapsed. This is used in UI
to show either the short version of the expandable value or the full, expanded one. It is part of the parsed type because performance of adding
it later on large models is really costly. This might change in the upcoming versions of this parser.

unions.name: SequenceType
unions.comment:
Sequence type

All List-like structures are the same, so we parsed them into `ElmSequence` type. However we would like to keep the information about which
type the sequence was.

values.name: hasNestedValues
values.comment: Determines whether value has any nested childrens.

unions.name: Path
unions.comment: Path to uniquely identify nested expandable value. It is used to e.g. toggle specific expandable value, so you can expand and collapse it.

values.name: indexFromPath
values.comment: Extracts index of nested value from it's path

values.name: initPath
values.comment: Initial path. It is used as the top level starting point

values.name: mapValuesWithPath
values.comment: Useful if you want to render nested values and you would like to make them clickable. Think of this as `List.mapIndex` but with Path instead of index.
values.type: DebugParser.Path.Path -> (DebugParser.Path.Path -> a -> b) -> List.List a -> List.List b

values.name: toggleValueByPath
values.comment: Given a path and a top level value you can expand and collapse nested expandable values.
